	limitations: [
		{description: "Legal review adds time and cost to every contract change, new feature with contractual implications, and new term.", alternative: "Tiered legal review by impact: contract template changes (always full review). New feature without contractual implications (no review). Feature that changes participant obligations (review required). New external-facing term with juridical risk (review). Prioritize: contracts > API terms > UI labels. ~80% of features need no legal review.", rationale: "Legal review by impact level. Not everything needs lawyer. But contracts always do."},
		{description: "Automated borderô/cessão generation requires validated templates that may vary by FIDC (each FIDC may have specific addendum requirements).", alternative: "Base template: Mesh standard (covers 90% of requirements). FIDC-specific addendum: configurable per FIDC (appended to base). System: generates base + appends FIDC addendum. Legal review: once per FIDC setup (not per operation). Maintenance: base template reviewed quarterly; addendums reviewed annually.", rationale: "Base + addendum = flexible without per-operation customization."},
		{description: "Digital signature integration (Clicksign/D4Sign) adds per-signature cost and third-party dependency.", alternative: "Cost: R$1-5 per signature — negligible vs R$50.000 operation value. Dependency: multiple Brazilian providers available (Clicksign, D4Sign, DocuSign Brazil) — portable if provider issues. For MVP/low volume: manual PDF + email exchange is functional (not ideal but legally valid as assinatura simples). Scale: integrate signature platform when volume justifies.", rationale: "Per-signature cost is rounding error. Multiple providers = no single-vendor dependency."},
		{description: "Contract-code alignment requires ongoing maintenance — every feature must check against contracts.", alternative: "Not every feature: only features that change state machines, create/modify operations, or affect participant obligations. Quarterly alignment audit (30 min: 3 transitions checked) catches drift. CLAUDE.md instruction: 'flag contractual implications.' Most PRs: no contractual impact. Few: flagged and reviewed.", rationale: "Quarterly audit + CLAUDE.md flagging > continuous review. Pragmatic for solo founder."},
		{description: "Dispute resolution via arbitragem is expensive (R$20.000+ initiation cost) and may be inaccessible for small participants.", alternative: "Escalation ladder filters 90% of disputes at lower levels (autoatendimento, suporte, mediação). Arbitragem: only for disputes >R$50.000 where stakes justify cost. Small disputes (<R$50.000): foro judicial (cheaper, more accessible). Most disputes: resolved operationally without reaching legal process. Track: % of disputes resolved at each level.", rationale: "Escalation ladder is key — most disputes never reach arbitragem. Arbitragem reserved for high-value."},
